It was a Birthday celebration and on the online booking request I had said could we order a ‘Cote de Boeuf experience’ and if it was unavailable on the night could I be informed prior to attending (the Birthday person specifically requested going to M&C for that reason)
No one had contacted me so one would have thought it would be available on the night requested.
On arrival the server seemed very stressed and hurried our order as she said one cote de boeuf was being held for us and she wanted to get it ordered as there was only 1 left.
After quickly ordering our food and then she returned with our drinks we asked for the wine which went with the experience. She snapped to say we hadn’t ordered the ‘experience’ only the cote de boeuf?!
For one she didn’t ask and another we then presumed our booking request had been read as she said on arrival ‘a cote de boeuf’ had been held for us?!
It all worked out in the end and the food was beautiful and cooked to perfection.
Please read any requests on the booking and perhaps if unsure or cannot meet requests the customer could be rung to confirm/decline before arrival?

data.text:
This is the third time we have visited the restaurant in Wilmslow.
The visit prior to this one, was also not a great experience. One of our steaks was way overcooked and so had to send it back, meaning I ate my food while my partner waited for his.
Although the waitress was very helpful it still wasn’t the experience we have come to expect from miller and Carter restaurants.
We were offered free deserts but declined as we were actually quite full.
More recently, we decided to give the restaurant another chance. We were given a warm welcome and taken to our table. The restaurant was very quiet which was odd as we were given a table crammed into the corner of a small section which was quite cosy with other guests.

We both ordered the steak experience which included a salad to start. The lettuce had brown patches which were slightly off putting. A simple task I would think to cut out by the chef.
The steaks arrived shortly after, both again were overcooked however the middle sections were a medium which we decided to eat.
The onion loaf was hard, difficult to cut and mushy in the middle. We waited at least 10 minutes for the waiter to come and see how our food was but nobody came I therefore had to go to the bar to ask the waiter if we could get two fresh pieces of the onion loaf. Within a few minutes the two onion loaf is arrived which look like they just come out the microwave as we’re still slightly steaming again this look like it was from the same batch as the ones we’ve just been given. I feel like the chef had not cooked this fresh for the day and it instead used the previous day or days batch’s.

We have frequented a few miller and Carter restaurants within the UK now and this is probably the only location where we have been disappointed with the standard of food. If I’m honest I feel like the chef has been quite lazy, as some of the same issues we had repeated themselves again.

It’s a shame as the service overall was good however the restaurant is being let down by the standard of food which the chef is overall responsible for.

Sadly we won’t be returning to the restaurant in Wilmslow, however we have not given up on the chain completely and will continue to visit miller and Carter restaurants elsewhere.

We went for our uncles 75th Birthday and wanted something special.  We chose this restaurant after a terrible visit to their Stockport branch and we were not disappointed!

Two people in our party were wheelchair users and had accessible vehicles which are quite large as they have gold out wheelchair ramps.  A staff member came out and helped us park these vehicles advising where would be best for us.  So the top class service started before we entered.

Food was excellent and I have an illness which means I eat very slowly.  They were very accommodating and didn’t rush the mains, they allowed me time to finish the starters and not be rushed. (Stockport branch brought the
Mains whilst I was still eating the starters!!).

This was the first time my uncle and my mum had been to a Miller and Carter although they had heard us talk about it often enough.

My uncle rated his fillet as “the second best steak he had ever had” (he said the best was one he made and so couldn’t say that was bad 😂.

My mum loved her meal and understood why we say good things about this venue.

My son was paralysed a few months ago and so has recently come out of rehabilitation.  I had promised him a steak when he came home and so he was a member of the party.  He had the T-Bone and loved it.

Staff were excellent and Amber even had a bit of banter with my uncle regarding his Guinness which he loved.  Amber was an excellent waitress and very friendly and patient.

Only slight downside was my wife missed the berries on her dessert that should have been with the dish.  Only a small oversight.

We would and will definitely return.

My wife and I visited Miller and Carter in Wilmslow on Christmas eve to celebrate our 21st wedding anniversary. We normally go to Miller and carter in Stockport where we have always had great service and excellent food.
Unfortunately our experience at Wilmslow was poor to say the least. we felt very rushed, the service was not up to the standard of Stockport. When our main courses were served we had no cutlery to eat with, as we had been sat in a quite corner it took 10 minutes for us to attract the attention of a member of staff. The quality of the the steak was tough and full of sinew. Having finished our meal we returned home. As  I got out of my car, we noticed the car had been damaged whilst park in the Miller and Carter car park. I have contacted Miller and Carter and was told that it happens all the time, and that she would check the CCTV.
She also told me she would call me a couple of days later. The young lady said she would confirm the vehicle which damaged my car and report it to the police. I have not heard back from Miller and Carter in Wilmslow. I have left several messages with no reply. I would highly recommend Miller and Carter in Stockport, and advise people not to bother with Wilmslow. Sorry to be negative, but what should have been a enjoyable night turned into a very expensive disaster.

I am sorry to hear that you were unhappy with your dining experience here with us back at Christmas time, and had you let us know on the evening we would have certainly tried to rectify any issues for you at the time rather than you leave unhappy. It was myself that you spoke to on the car park that evening, and I explained to you that I can only give the CCTV footage to the police when they request it from me directly, I do not make the calls to the police on your behalf unfortunately. If you wish to pursue this through the police then I am more happy to provide them with any footage that they may require from me. All cars are parked in our car park at your own risk, as with most car parks. I am however sorry to hear that damage was caused to your vehicle on that evening.

data.text:
Where to start...
Every once in awhile you come across a marbled gem, this was one such occasion. The quality of the meat was superb and it sliced as if it had been requested by the gods themselves, just the right amount of blood dripped from the steak, shyly though, almost asking your permission to do so, my permission was granted.
The flavour danced across my palate like pre-raphaelite cherubs dance across an oyster in those, frankly odd, cartoons of yore. Leaving you with a desire to exhale heartily while savouring each morsal. Accompanied by a superb selection of expertly prepared sides (I chose those though so you can't have credit for this :p) all culminating in me over eating and returning home to sleep of what was the most enjoyable meal of this year so far!

Well done guys.
